-- Magna to Develop Opel Astra Model for General Motors, Handelsblatt Reports
-- B y   J e r e m y   v a n   L o o n
-- 2010-09-28T05:36:58Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-28/magna-to-develop-opel-astra-model-for-general-motors-handelsblatt-reports.html
Magna International Inc.  is close
to reaching an agreement with  General Motors Co . to develop a
convertible version of Opel Astra,  Handelsblatt  reported.  The Canadian parts supplier and GM are attempting “a new
beginning” after the U.S. carmaker decided not to sell its Opel
division to Magna last year, damaging the relationship, the
newspaper said, citing unidentified company officials.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jeremy van Loon in Berlin at 
 jvanloon@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Reed Landberg at 
 landberg@bloomberg.net  